genresAdvancedInfo.name: classic female blues
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre of music emerged in the early 20th century and is characterized by its raw, emotional vocals and soulful instrumentation. Classic female blues often deals with themes of love, heartbreak, and struggle, with artists like Bessie Smith and Ma Rainey paving the way for future generations of female blues singers. This genre has had a profound impact on the development of modern music, influencing everything from rock and roll to R&B.
